ONE person has been killed and another injured in a drive by
shooting, on Neptune Drive in Verulam KwaZulu Natal on Friday morning. According to Reaction Unit South Africa (Rusa) spokesperson
Prem Balram, at about 06:12 RUSA officers were called out to the scene after
receiving multiple calls from the public reporting shots being fired in the
area. "Upon arrival it was established that a family of five
which included two females were on their way to work in Umhlanga - KZN when the
occupants of a white Fiat Uno pulled up next to their Mazda 3 and opened fire
on them. "The driver was shot in the leg while the front seat
passenger was shot in the head," Balram said. It's reported the victims then sped off and stopped at a
general dealer for assistance. Balram Â said the two
injured men were rushed to a private hospital. On arrival one of the men were declared dead, while the
second victim was treated for a gunshot wound to his leg. The victims are allegedly residents of Trenance Park in
Verulam and the motive for the shooting is yet to be established. 